BFN 

  [Text] Pretoria May 23 SAPA -- The government was formally 
informed on Monday of South Africa's acceptance as a member of 
the Organisation of African Unity. Foreign Affairs Minister 
Alfred Nzo said in a statement OAU Secretary-General Dr Salim 
Salim had informed the government of the OAU's consensus to 
accept South Africa as a member. 
  Mr Nzo is to visit Addis Adaba on Wednesday for the official 
raising of the South African flag at OAU headquarters. 

